    <p>
      I'm a fan of fast-loading websites and apps, and I'm always on the lookout for ways to increase page speed while respecting brand identity guidelines. In the case of <a href="https://developers.google.com/speed/pagespeed/insights/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cartalk.com%2Fcar-donation%2Fcalifornia%2F" target="_blank">Car Talk's Vehicle Donation Program</a>, I managed to get their page speed scores up to 96-99% on mobile by strategically using things like CSS gradients, inline SVGs, and the Jamstack.
    </p>
    <figure class="full-bleed">
      <img src="/images/portfolio/ui-ux/car-talk.png" loading="lazy" width="1472" height="1217" class="box-shadow">
