    <p>
      In 2015, I created a "periodic table" of New Hampshire's 4000-foot mountains with the intention of gifting it to one or two friends. One of those friends encouraged me to sell them, so I took a chance and paid for a <em>daunting</em> print run of 500 copies. They sold out in a matter of weeks. Since then, I've expanded the concept, produced a series of hiking passports, and created a letterpress line. One thing is for sure: I've learned a lot about how to use variable data in Adobe Illustrator.
    </p>
    <figure class="full-bleed">
      <img src="/images/portfolio/print/periodic-table-of-ski-resorts.png" loading="lazy" width="2400" height="1610">
      <figcaption>
